// Broadcast-minimization idiom (M1 + s1) + (M2 + s2), which the compiler
// regroups to (M1 + M2) + (s1 + s2). The scalars are near 2^62 so their sum
// overflows si64; integer addition is associative in Z/2^64, so the regrouping
// preserves the wraparound and the result matches the reference exactly.

M1 = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6];
M1 = reshape(M1, 2, 3);
M2 = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50, 60];
M2 = reshape(M2, 2, 3);

s1 = 4611686018427387904;
s2 = 4611686018427387905;

print((M1 + s1) + (M2 + s2));
